The paper deals with regular languages and automata, which are fundamental concepts in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also discusses the concept of numeration systems, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DS). The study of the properties of infinite sequences generated by automata falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the study of computational complexity (cs.CC) as it deals with the enumeration of words in an infinite regular language.
